http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Tributes-paid-to-Bardhan/article13980049.ece

The Telangana and AP committees of Communist Party of India (CPI) on Sunday paid rich tributes to veteran party leader and former general secretary A.B. Bardhan at New Delhi on Saturday.At a meeting held in Makhdoom Bhavan here, party leaders led by its State secretary Chada Venkat Reddy recollected Bardhan’s services to the party and his role in struggles taken up for basic needs to the poor, including health and education facilities and for the rights of working classes. They also hailed Bardhan’s role in the building the student movement in the country and his initiatives for joint struggles of the Left parties. Meanwhile, in a statement, Telangana committee of Communist Party of India (Marxist) also paid tributes to Bardhan. Polit Bureau member B.V. Raghavulu, State secretary Tammineni Veerabhadram, veteran leader Mallu Swarajyam and others recollected Bardhan’s role in the Communist movement.